Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE Agribusiness is pleased to present for sale “Mugga”, one of the largest Rural Leases within the Australian Capital Territory. Mugga represents an opportunity to acquire a well-developed rural lifestyle landholding with measurable productive capability situated within the confines of suburban Canberra.

KEY FEATURES OF MUGGA INCLUDE:

-	One of the largest Rural Leases within the Australian Capital Territory.
-	An enviable rural lifestyle opportunity embedded within suburban Canberra providing an unparalleled balance of rural lifestyle with city convenience. 
-	Ninety-nine-year lease commenced on 27 November 2006.
-	A substantial 312* hectare landholding previously utilised for cattle breeding and fattening.
-	Attractive, gently undulating grazing landscape rising to granite torr hills with commanding views over Canberra to the north.
-	Attractive, gently undulating grazing landscape rising to granite torr hills with commanding views over Canberra to the north.
-	Working improvements including shearing shed and sheep yards, machinery sheds, hay sheds and cattle yards. 
-	Multiple accommodation options including the executive homestead featuring four bedrooms, two bathrooms, formal dining and lounge rooms and three-car garage set in attractive gardens with in-ground pool. A second three-bedroom home currently provides rental income. The single room demountable provides a facility to use as a farm office or small accommodation option. 

Mugga represents a unique opportunity for an aspiring purchaser to acquire a once-in-a-generation asset featuring real enterprise scale in an enviable location within metropolitan Canberra. 

Mugga is being offered for sale by tender closing on Thursday 7th December 2017 at 4.00pm AEDT
